com.wingfoot.soap.encoding
Interface TypeDeserializer

All Known Implementing Classes:
ComplexTypeDeserializer
public interface TypeDeserializer

Defines properties that are required to convert a parameter to a Java object based on the rules defined in XML schema. Custom type deserializers implement this interface.

unmarshall

public void unmarshall(Type schemaComponent,
                       java.lang.Object javaBean,
                       org.kxml.parser.XmlParser parser,
                       SOAPDeserializer deserializer,
                       WSDLHolder wsdlHolder)
                throws SOAPException
Converts parameters in the parser to Java objects based on the definition in the Component.
Parameters:
schemaComponent - the Type that contains the definition of the parameter
javaBean - Object where the properties of the complexType has to be written to.
parser - XmlParser that contains the payload. The parser is pointing to the start tag of the parameter.
deserializer - SOAPDeserializer that is the entry point to deserializing a parameter.
wsdlHolder - WSDLHolder that encapsulates the WSDL.
Throws:
SOAPException - if any error occurs during deserialization
